@node MAIN "Welcome"

  Welcome to the world of @{b}FlashMandel-ARexx!@{ub}

  This guide supports you to write arexx-scripts for FlashMandelNG. Please notice, that on the following pages only the
  special features of the FlashMandelNG-arexx are explained. If you are not familiar with the basic arexx-syntax,
  please refer the arexx-manual distributed with the most Amiga-computers (or something like that ;-) ).


    @{"general" link GENERAL}                  general informations for writing scripts for FlashMandelNG.
    @{"commands" link COMMANDS}                 list of all commands implemented in FlashMandelNG.
    @{"examples" link EXAMPLES}                 the example-scripts.
    @{"problems" link PROBLEMS}                 when arexx refuses to work.


  Important:

  Please notice the new API for some commands in FlashMandelNG! All affected commands are marked with "changed in FlashMandelNG".

@endnode
@node GENERAL "general informations"

  General informations to FlashMandelNG-arexx:


  * Where to @{b}store@{ub} the scripts

    The standard-path is "FLASHMANDEL:arexx". It is easier for you, when you store all script into this drawer.

  * The @{b}hostname@{ub}

    The hostname is allways spelled like this: @{b}FLASHMANDEL.n@{ub}, The first launched process has n = 1, the second n = 2 and
    so on...

  * How to @{b}launch@{ub} a script

    There are several possibilities for this:

    1. Of course you can start a script by typing it into a shell. For example:

       > rx FLASHMANDEL:arexx/test.rexx FLASHMANDEL.1

    2. You can choose the menu-item "ARexx/Launch...". After this a asl-filerequester appears, where you can click onto the script
       you want to start.

    3. You can create a sub-item in the arexx-menu by using the icon-tooltypes. The first should have the name REXXCMD.1, the next
       REXXCMD.2 and so on...
       There is no limit to the number of menu-items - only the limits of the AmigaOS.

    @{b}@{u}IMPORTANT:@{uu}@{ub}

    Every script started from FlashMandelNG, gets the actual arexx-hostname as the first argument. So you can always set the correct
    hostname, if you have started FlashMandelNG several times.

  * If there is a special arexx-script named "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/startup.rexx", it will be launched at starttime of FlashMandelNG.
    Usefull to configure FlashMandelNG or for playing a background-sound or ...


@endnode
@node PROBLEMS "problems"

  Problems with FlashMandelNG-arexx:

  * FlashMandelNG uses the reaction-arexx-class. Because of this you need AmigaOS 3.5+ to use this functionality - sorry.
    It is not planned to support lower versions,
    But: Why not updating your system - with OS 3.5+ you will have a modern reaction-GUI as well!

  * No more known problems.

@endnode
@node EXAMPLES "examples"

  Examples distributed with FlashMandelNG:

  * @{"Benchmark_II.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/_benchmark_ii.rexx/Main"}:

    A script to make some benchmarks with FlashMandel. You can choose between several options. Needs AWNPipe for the GUI.
    (Is fully localized and remembers the last settings).

  * @{"Create_FMandel_Anim.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/_create_fmandel_anim.rexx/Main"}:

    Creates an IFF-animation. Opens a AWNPipe-GUI, where you can choose between several options (anim-type, scaling...)
    (Is fully localized and remembers the last settings).

  * @{"Toolbar.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/_toolbar.rexx/Main"}:

    Opens a toolbar on the FlashMandel-screen including the most important functions. Probably you can launch this script
    using 'startup.rexx'. Needs AWNPipe for the GUI.
    (Is fully localized and remembers the last settings).

  * @{"PlayMovie.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/PlayMovie.rexx/Main"}:

    Just makes some zooms into your actual picture.

  * @{"RunningColor.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/RunningColor.rexx/Main"}:

    Shows you, how to manipulate the palette. It just moves a color through the palette.

  * @{"startup.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/startup.rexx/Main"}:

    example-statup-script for FlashMandelNG. Will be executed at starttime and plays the welcome sound.

  * @{"StopSound.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/StopSound.rexx/Main"}:

    Just stops playing a sound.

  * @{"Test_ARexx.rexx" link "FLASHMANDEL:arexx/Test_ARexx.rexx/Main"}:

    Here you can find example-code for all arexx-commands implemented in FlashMandelNG. If you want to test a command, you have to set
    the "IF 0"-line to "IF 1".


@endnode
@node COMMANDS "Welcome"

  Here is a list of all arexx-commands implemented in FlashMandelNG:

  @{u}Project-commands:@{uu}

  @{"ABOUT" link AREXX-COMMAND_ABOUT}                 Open about-requester.
  @{"SYSINFO" link AREXX-COMMAND_SYSINFO}               Open system-info-requester.
  @{"HELP" link AREXX-COMMAND_HELP}                  Open help-guide.
  @{"LOAD_PICTURE" link AREXX-COMMAND_LOAD_PICTURE}          Load a picture.
  @{"SAVE_PICTURE" link AREXX-COMMAND_SAVE_PICTURE}          Save a picture.
  @{"LOAD_PALETTE" link AREXX-COMMAND_LOAD_PALETTE}          Load a palette.
  @{"SAVE_PALETTE" link AREXX-COMMAND_SAVE_PALETTE}          Save a palette.
  @{"PRINT" link AREXX-COMMAND_PRINT}                 Print picture.
  @{"QUIT" link AREXX-COMMAND_QUIT}                  Quit FlashMandelNG

  @{u}Options-commands:@{uu}

  @{"SHOW_TITLE" link AREXX-COMMAND_SHOW_TITLE}            Toggle screen-title.
  @{"SHOW_ELAPSED" link AREXX-COMMAND_SHOW_ELAPSED}          Show elapsed time.
  @{"SET_COORDINATES" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_COORDINATES}       Set complex-coordinates.
  @{"GET_COORDINATES" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_COORDINATES}       Get complex-coordinates.
  @{"SET_ITERATIONS" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_ITERATIONS}        Set number of iterations.
  @{"GET_ITERATIONS" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_ITERATIONS}        Get number of iterations.
  @{"SET_POWER" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_POWER}             Set power-parameter.
  @{"GET_POWER" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_POWER}             Get power-parameter.
  @{"SET_PRIORITY" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_PRIORITY}          Set task-priority.
  @{"GET_PRIORITY" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_PRIORITY}          Get task-priority.
  @{"SET_COLOR_REMAP" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_COLOR_REMAP}       Set color-remap-method.
  @{"GET_COLOR_REMAP" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_COLOR_REMAP}       Get color-remap-method.
  @{"SET_FRACTAL_TYPE" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_FRACTAL_TYPE}      Set fractal-type (Julia/Mandelbrot).
  @{"GET_FRACTAL_TYPE" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_FRACTAL_TYPE}      Get fractal-type (Julia/Mandelbrot).
  @{"SET_CPU_TYPE" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_CPU_TYPE}          Set cpu-type (68k/PPC)
  @{"GET_CPU_TYPE" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_CPU_TYPE}          Get cpu-time (68k/PPC)

  @{u}calculation-commands:@{uu}

  @{"SHOW_PREVIEW" link AREXX-COMMAND_SHOW_PREVIEW}          Open preview-window.
  @{"RENDER" link AREXX-COMMAND_RENDER}                Render fractal.
  @{"UNDO" link AREXX-COMMAND_UNDO}                  Undo last changes.
  @{"SET_FRAME" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_FRAME}             Set zoom-frame.
  @{"GET_FRAME" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_FRAME}             Get zoom-frame.

  @{u}video-commands:@{uu}

  @{"ZOOM" link AREXX-COMMAND_ZOOM}                  Zoom into the picture.
  @{"DO_COLORCYCLING" link AREXX-COMMAND_DO_COLORCYCLING}       Start color-cycling.
  @{"SET_DELAY" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_DELAY}             Set delay-time for color-cycling.
  @{"GET_DELAY" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_DELAY}             Get delay-time for color-cycling.
  @{"SET_PALETTE" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_PALETTE}           Set screen-palette. @{b}(changed in FlashMandelNG)@{ub}
  @{"GET_PALETTE" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_PALETTE}           Get screen-palette. @{b}(changed in FlashMandelNG)@{ub}
  @{"SET_SCREENATTRS" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_SCREENATTRS}       Set screen-attributes. @{b}(changed in FlashMandelNG)@{ub}
  @{"GET_SCREENATTRS" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_SCREENATTRS}       Get screen-attributes. @{b}(changed in FlashMandelNG)@{ub}
  @{"SET_FONT" link AREXX-COMMAND_SET_FONT}              Set screen-font.
  @{"GET_FONT" link AREXX-COMMAND_GET_FONT}              Get screen-font.

  @{u}misc-commands:@{uu}
  
  @{"START_TIMER" link AREXX-COMMAND_START_TIMER}           Start timer.
  @{"STOP_TIMER" link AREXX-COMMAND_STOP_TIMER}            Stop timer.
  @{"PLAY_SOUND" link AREXX-COMMAND_PLAY_SOUND}            Play a datatype-sound.
  @{"STOP_SOUND" link AREXX-COMMAND_STOP_SOUND}            Stop sound.

